sentences: Laleh Pourkarim (Persian: لاله پورکریم, IPA: [lɒːleje puːɾkæɾiːm]; born 10 June 1982), known mononymously as Laleh (Swedish: [ˈlɑ̌ːlɛ]), is an Iranian-Swedish singer-songwriter, record producer, guitarist, pianist, actress and record company manager.

Following a short acting career, she entered the music industry in 2005 with her self-titled debut album, which peaked at number one in Sweden and went on to become that country's the highest selling album of the year.
In 2011, she participated in the Swedish television show Så mycket bättre, which sees a number of artists create new interpretations of the others' songs.
Her 2012 album, Sjung, was released across Scandinavia on 25 January 2012 to generally positive reviews.

Colors, was released across Scandinavia in October 2013.
She signed to Island Records in January 2014, and followed with the September 2014 release of the Boom EP.
In 2016 she released the album Kristaller and in 2019 the album Vänta!.

She is the daughter of Houshang Pourkarim, who died in 1994.

sentences: Following a short acting career, she entered the music industry in 2005 with her self-titled debut album, which peaked at number one in Sweden and went on to become that country's the highest selling album of the year.

The lead single from Sjung, "Some Die Young", was a commercial hit across Scandinavia, peaking at number one in Norway for eight weeks and becoming the twentieth biggest selling single of all time in the country.
She signed to Island Records in January 2014, and followed with the September 2014 release of the Boom EP.

Laleh was born in the Northern Iranian harbour town of Bandar-e Anzali, but fled the country a year later with her parents to live in Azerbaijan, and later moving on to Minsk and a refugee camp in Tidaholm.
